==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: adaptive optics
<hw>adaptive optics</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>an
optical system used in some telescopes since the 1980's which rapidly
changes the shape of the primary reflecting mirror to adjust for
distortions of light which are caused by atmospheric turbulence. By
reducing the distortions caused by the atmosphere, telescopes fitted
with such optics can achieve a higher resolving power than normal
telescopes with static mirrors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>adaptive radiation</ent>⟦br⟧
